The paper discusses the use of autoassociative neural networks (ANNs) for noise reduction in geophysical data, specifically seismic data. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep-stacked-autoNNs, which suggests a focus on deep learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the processing of data, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves the reduction of noise, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound).
